<ContentLayout title="About Abelost" description="A small, independent collection of practical calculators built to make everyday estimates easier to understand.">
  <h2>Useful before impressive</h2>
  <p>Abelost exists to answer the small but consequential questions that appear during a project or decision: how much material should I order, what will this appliance cost to run, or what price covers my business costs?</p>
  <p>Each tool is designed around a focused question. We show the formula, expose the important assumptions, and explain where the estimate stops being reliable.</p>
  <h2>What we build</h2>
  <p>The current collection covers home improvement, yard and garden projects, household energy, vehicle costs, and small-business planning. Tools are free to use and require no account.</p>
  <h2>How the site is funded</h2>
  <p>Abelost may use clearly identified advertising to support its operation. Advertising does not change calculator results. We do not accept payment to manipulate formulas or estimates.</p>
  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>If you find a calculation problem or unclear assumption, email <a href="mailto:hello@abelost.com">hello@abelost.com</a>. Include the calculator name and an example input so the issue can be reproduced.</p>
</ContentLayout>
